item.title: Lenny Kaye
item.description: Lenny Kaye is an American guitarist, composer, and writer who is best known as a member of the Patti Smith Group.

item.title: Ivan Kral
item.description: Ivan Král is a Czech-born American composer, filmmaker, record producer, bass guitar player, and singer-songwriter. He works across genres including punk, rock, jazz, soul, country and film scores. His songs have been recorded by such artists as U2, Pearl Jam, Téléphone, Patti Smith, Iggy Pop, David Bowie, Simple Minds, First Aid Kit, and John Waite, among others.

item.title: Patti Smith
item.description: Patricia Lee Smith is an American singer-songwriter, musician, author, and poet who became an influential component of the New York City punk rock movement with her 1975 debut album Horses.
